        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/4231798668?book_show_action=true">Dec 30, 2021</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Aroub Al-Shalabi" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Aroub Al-Shalabi" href="/user/show/107422888-aroub-al-shalabi">Aroub Al-Shalabi</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/107422888-aroub-al-shalabi?shelf=islamic">islamic</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer4231798668" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer6693815177684356211">Have you ever thought about the reason behind the existence of Humans?<br/>Why were we created? Who created us? <br/>What can we do ? <br/>Can we truly find purpose?<br/>What is the end ? <br/>Death... Life... Beginning The End....<br/>This Book is abut a conversation between an ashiest and an ex-ashiest <br/>The author happens to be one of the most influential in our time ,a Physician, author, Muslim scholar and reformer who had made an adventure of his life to discover more than meets the eye <br/>Quote from Wikipedia &quot;starting with</span>
  <span id="freeText6693815177684356211" style="display:none">Have you ever thought about the reason behind the existence of Humans?<br />Why were we created? Who created us? <br />What can we do ? <br />Can we truly find purpose?<br />What is the end ? <br />Death... Life... Beginning The End....<br />This Book is abut a conversation between an ashiest and an ex-ashiest <br />The author happens to be one of the most influential in our time ,a Physician, author, Muslim scholar and reformer who had made an adventure of his life to discover more than meets the eye <br />Quote from Wikipedia "starting with his journeys to the Tropics in Tanzania, Uganda, Kenya, and the south of Sudan, where he stayed for two months with the tribe of Niam Niam. Thereafter, he traveled to the Sahara Desert, to the oasis of Ghadamis, where he stayed for a month with the tribe of El Tawariq. Furthermore, he traveled to many capitals of European and American countries, such as: Italy, Germany, Greece, France, Canada and the United States; and to the Arab countries, beginning with Morocco and Algeria in the west; and ending with Lebanon, Syria and Saudi Arabia in the east."<br />Exactly the kind of person you want to read about and read for &lt;3 ! <br /> </span>
  <a data-text-id="6693815177684356211" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


